cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a procedure for learning optimized policies using A/B testing data. It also involves the use of inverse-propensity-weighting effect estimator, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with optimizing policies and maximizing rewards. The sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also possible as the paper discusses the cost and risks associated with deploying policies. The sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are less likely but still possible as the paper involves the use of bagging process and out-of-bag policy inclusion decisions.
